Validated against:
- Zero index overlap between train/test splits (checked directly on the Subset indices)
- A synthetic dataset with a deliberately-imposed ~85% accuracy ceiling (15% of samples
  per class carry another class's signal pattern but keep their true label) -- the
  pipeline correctly plateaued at ~82-84% and never exceeded the imposed ceiling,
  ruling out train/test leakage in the code.
- A chronological (non-random) train/test split -- first 80% of each class's samples
  (in on-disk order) as train, last 20% as test -- to rule out the model exploiting
  recording-session artifacts rather than the actual fault signature. Accuracy held at
  100% under this stricter split too.
- Per-file label integrity check on the raw .mat files: each of the 6 files contains a
  single constant label value, and the six values are exactly {0,1,2,3,4,5} with no
  duplicates or gaps.
